  "texts": [
    "Finally, researchers new to eye track-ing will benefit from reading the article from the beginning to the end.",
    "Readers new to eye tracking may find unfamiliar terms in this article, for instance gaze, fixation, and head-free eyetracker setup.",
    "If such terms are encountered, we refer the reader to Table 1, which gives a brief explanation of the terms and points the reader to relevant articles or later sections in the article where the terms are described in more detail.",
    "Some general considerations apply to everyone considering choosing an eye tracker, may not be directly related to the intended research question and participant group, and may also apply to instruments other than eye trackers.",
    "They include (in no particular order):"
  ]
